  "texts": [
    "Past efforts in this domain have largely focused on refining the linguistic capabilities of LLMs, enhancing their understanding of syntax, semantics, and the broader context of language [7,8,2,9,1,10].",
    "While these efforts have significantly improved the general linguistic proficiency of LLMs, they have not sufficiently addressed the issue of tailored information retrieval [11,2].",
    "The current models often retrieve information that, while linguistically coherent, may not be entirely relevant or accurate in response to specific user queries, which can be either error in information retrieval or hallucinations [12,9,13,14,15].",
    "This gap highlights a need for a more focused approach to optimize information retrieval in these models.Recognizing this need, the present study proposes a novel approach by integrating reinforcement learning into the LLaMA model to enhance its information retrieval accuracy.",
    "Reinforcement learning, a branch of machine learning, involves an algorithm learning to make decisions through a process of reward and feedback."
  ],
